---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Installation - sls.tf">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="docs-header">
      <h1>Installation</h1>
      <p class="docs-description">
        How to install and set up sls.tf in your project
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
        <p>
          Before you begin, make sure you have the following tools installed:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Terraform (v1.0+)</strong> - For infrastructure deployment</li>
          <li><strong>Node.js (v16+)</strong> - For development and testing</li>
          <li><strong>Git</strong> - For version control</li>
          <li><strong>AWS CLI</strong> - Configured with appropriate credentials</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Quick Start</h2>
        <p>
          The fastest way to get started with sls.tf is to add it as a submodule to your existing project:
        </p>

        <div class="code-block">
          <h4>Add sls.tf submodule</h4>
          <pre><code># Add the sls.tf submodule to your project
git submodule add https://github.com/your-org/sls.tf.git modules/sls.tf
git submodule update --init --recursive</code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="code-block">
          <h4>Initialize Terraform</h4>
          <pre><code># Navigate to your project directory
cd your-project

# Initialize Terraform
terraform init

# Plan your infrastructure
terraform plan

# Apply the changes
terraform apply</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Manual Installation</h2>
        <p>
          If you prefer not to use Git submodules, you can manually download and include sls.tf:
        </p>

        <div class="code-block">
          <h4>Download and setup</h4>
          <pre><code># Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-org/sls.tf.git

# Copy to your project modules directory
cp -r sls.tf /path/to/your-project/modules/

# Navigate to your project
cd /path/to/your-project

# Initialize Terraform
terraform init</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Basic Configuration</h2>
        <p>
          Create a simple Terraform configuration to use sls.tf:
        </p>

        <div class="code-block">
          <h4>main.tf</h4>
          <pre><code>terraform {'{'}
  required_version = ">= 1.0"
  required_providers {'{'}
    aws = {'{'}
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = "~> 5.0"
    {'}'}
  {'}'}
{'}'}

provider "aws" {'{'}
  region = "us-east-1"
{'}'}

module "serverless" {'{'}
  source = "./modules/sls.tf"

  # Path to your serverless.yml file
  config_file = "${path.root}/serverless.yml"

  # AWS region for deployment
  region = "us-east-1"

  # Environment variables
  environment = "production"
{'}'}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Configuration File</h2>
        <p>
          Make sure you have a serverless.yml file in your project root:
        </p>

        <div class="code-block">
          <h4>serverless.yml</h4>
          <pre><code>service: my-api
provider:
  name: aws
  runtime: nodejs18.x
  region: us-east-1

functions:
  hello:
    handler: handler.hello
    events:
      - http:
          path: hello
          method: get</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Verification</h2>
        <p>
          After installation, verify everything is working correctly:
        </p>

        <div class="code-block">
          <h4>Test the installation</h4>
          <pre><code># Check Terraform configuration
terraform validate

# See what will be created
terraform plan

# If everything looks good, apply
terraform apply</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Next Steps</h2>
        <p>
          Once you have sls.tf installed and working, check out these guides:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/docs/configuration">Configuration Guide</a> - Advanced configuration options</li>
          <li><a href="/docs/examples/basic-service">Basic Example</a> - Complete working example</li>
          <li><a href="/docs/features/typescript">TypeScript Support</a> - Using TypeScript configurations</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .docs-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .docs-header h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1a202c;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .docs-description {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: #4a5568;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .content {
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .section h2 {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1a202c;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #e2e8f0;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section h4 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #2d3748;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .section p {
    color: #4a5568;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .section ul {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .section li {
    color: #4a5568;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section a {
    color: #667eea;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .section a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .code-block {
    background: #f7fafc;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .code-block pre {
    background: #1a202c;
    color: #e2e8f0;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 0;
    font-family: 'Monaco', 'Menlo', 'Ubuntu Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .code-block code {
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
    color: inherit;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .container {
      padding: 1rem;
    }

    .docs-header h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .section h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .code-block {
      padding: 1rem;
    }

    .code-block pre {
      font-size: 0.8rem;
    }
  }
</style>